{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "Implemented prompt 55 end to end. The backend now persists selected continuity revisions, refreshes them from accepted planning/composition state, hydrates them into session snapshots, and carries continuity payloads into composition/rew...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_240", "text": "Implemented prompt 55 end to end. The backend now persists selected continuity revisions, refreshes them from accepted planning/composition state, hydrates them into session snapshots, and carries continuity payloads into composition/rewrite jobs. The frontend now exposes that continuity bible as a grouped workspace inspector. I checkpointed the work in `ffe3107` and `dae6afd`.\n\nVerification passed on the touched surface: targeted backend `ruff`, targeted backend `pytest` (`51 passed`), frontend Vitest for the workspace page (`32 passed`), frontend lint, frontend build, and a browser QA run against the Docker Compose stack after applying the new migration in the dev container. The browser spec and screenshot are at [.artifacts/webapp-qa/continuity-inspector.spec.json](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/continuity-inspector.spec.json) and [.artifacts/webapp-qa/continuity-inspector.png](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.artifacts/webapp-qa/continuity-inspector.png).\n\nThe required reviewer summary has been written to [summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.yolopilot/runs/20260331T205548_storyteller_prompt_pack/55_continuity_bible_and_world_state_tracker/summary.md). The only remaining unstaged files are YoloPilot automation log/status files outside the feature itself.", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 486, "prompt_index": 56, "prompt_name": "55 \u2014 Continuity Bible and World-State Tracker", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-02T04:14:08-07:00"}
